definition: West Point, US military academy in New York
the West/abbr. for Spain 西班牙[Xi1 ban1 ya2]/Spanish

point/dot/drop/speck/o'clock/point (in space or time)/to draw a dot/to check on a list/to choose/to order (food in a restaurant)/to touch briefly/to hint/to light/to ignite/to pour a liquid drop by drop/(old) one fifth of a two-hour watch 更[geng1]/dot stroke in Chinese characters/classifier for items

sentences.english: They explained, We want to show our son what he missed by not coming to West Point.
sentences.chinese: 我们想让儿子知道他没来西点军校错过了什么。

sentences.english: Did you know that the farthest point east and the farthest point west in the United States are both in Alaska?
sentences.chinese: 你知道美国的最东点和最西点都是在阿拉斯加吗？

sentences.english: Her boyfriend is a cadet of West Point.
sentences.chinese: 她的男朋友是西点军校的一名军校生。

sentences.english: West Point is a 4-year school in New York State that educates future Army officers.
sentences.chinese: 西点是一所纽约州培养军官4年制的学校。

sentences.english: West Point and Volongze Military Academy are two of them.
sentences.chinese: 西点军校和伏龙芝军事学院就是其中的两所。

sentences.english: Sandhurst In England and West Point in the U. S. are military academies.
sentences.chinese: 英国的桑德赫斯特和美国的西点都是军事学院。

sentences.english: In 1842, Jackson enrolled at the U.S. Military Academy at West Point.
sentences.chinese: 1842年，杰克逊进入西点军校美国陆军军官学校。

sentences.english: He moved his headquarters to West Point in 1779 in the middle of the war.
sentences.chinese: 在1779年战争中期，他将作战总部转移到了西点。

sentences.english: I decided to study Patisserie and realized my dream.
sentences.chinese: 我决定去那里学习西点，实现我的梦想。

sentences.english: Was it harder to be a woman at West Point?
sentences.chinese: 在西点军校生存对女性而言难不难？

sentences.english: He says the presence of international students at West Point serves a purpose for the Army.
sentences.chinese: 他还说，目前西点军校的国际生都是为了军队服役的。

sentences.english: West Point cadets listened Tuesday evening as President Barack Obama, speaking in West Point, N. Y.
sentences.chinese: 西点军校的士官生在听奥巴马总统的演讲，纽约。
